        },
        {
          "id": "N_NARR_LOOK_STATIONS",
          "next": "N_REDIRECT_HUB",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Checkpoint dressed up as a work area: reader loop, dummy mass fixture, test load panel, and a clipboard station that looks like it\u2019s never been cleaned without being photographed first.\nThe supervisor doesn\u2019t step in your way. They just stand where your options feel narrower.",
          "type": "npc_line"
        },
        {
          "choices": [
            {
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act2.staging.amrClipped",
                  "op": "!=",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "effects": [
                {
                  "action": "set",
                  "key": "act2.staging.amrClipped",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "id": "C_USE_AMR_CLIP",
              "next": "N_AMR_CLIPPED",
              "text": "use: Clip the AMR tag into the reader loop."
            },
            {
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act2.staging.amrClipped",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "id": "C_USE_AMR_CLIP_ALREADY",
              "next": "N_AMR_ALREADY",
              "text": "use: Check the AMR tag seating again."
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_AMR_AUTH",
              "next": "N_AMR_AUTH",
              "text": "ask: What does the AMR actually authorize?"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_AMR_ARROW",
              "next": "N_AMR_ARROW",
              "text": "ask: If it reads either way, why the arrow?"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE_AMR_BACK",
              "next": "N_REDIRECT_HUB",
              "text": "leave: Back to staging."
            }
          ],
          "id": "N_AMR_MENU",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "type": "player_choice"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_AMR_CLIPPED",
          "next": "N_AMR_CLIPPED_SUP",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The tag seats with a small click.\nThe loop chirps once\u2014polite, like it\u2019s acknowledging a witness, not a worker.",
          "type": "npc_line"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_AMR_CLIPPED_SUP",
          "next": "N_AMR_BACK_MENU",
          "speakerId": "BAY_SUPERVISOR",
          "text": "AMR recognized. (pause)\nI'm logging it. That's all. (pause)\nApproval lives elsewhere\u2014 not in this room.",
          "type": "npc_line"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_AMR_ALREADY",
          "next": "N_AMR_BACK_MENU",
          "speakerId": "BAY_SUPERVISOR",
          "text": "It's seated. Leave it. Fiddling just adds entries.",
          "type": "npc_line"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_AMR_AUTH",
          "next": "N_AMR_BACK_MENU",
          "speakerId": "BAY_SUPERVISOR",
          "text": "It puts your name on the touch (pause) when the logs print. (pause)\nIt tags the touch as maintenance (pause) so it doesn\u2019t read as interference. (pause)\nThe machine couldn\u2019t care less. (pause) Committees do.",
          "type": "npc_line"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_AMR_ARROW",
          "next": "N_AMR_BACK_MENU",
          "speakerId": "BAY_SUPERVISOR",
          "text": "Because the arrow keeps the log consistent. (pause)\nOne way. Every time. (pause)\nConsistent reads boring. (pause)\nBoring keeps the site open. (pause)\nLong enough to finish.",
          "type": "npc_line"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_AMR_BACK_MENU",
          "target": "N_AMR_MENU",
          "type": "redirect"
        },
        {
          "choices": [
            {
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act2.staging.amrClipped",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": true
                },
                {
                  "key": "act2.staging.dummySeated",
                  "op": "!=",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "effects": [
                {
                  "action": "set",
                  "key": "act2.staging.dummySeated",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "id": "C_USE_DUMMY_SEAT_OK",
              "next": "N_DUMMY_SEATED",
              "text": "use: Seat the dummy mass fixture per card."
            },
            {
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act2.staging.amrClipped",
                  "op": "!=",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "id": "C_USE_DUMMY_SEAT_OOS",
              "next": "N_OOS_DUMMY",
              "text": "use: Seat the dummy mass fixture now (out of sequence)."
            },
            {
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act2.staging.dummySeated",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "id": "C_USE_DUMMY_ALREADY",
              "next": "N_DUMMY_ALREADY",
              "text": "use: Re-check the dummy mass latch."
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_DUMMY_UNITS",
              "next": "N_DUMMY_UNITS",
              "text": "ask: Who changed the units?"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_DUMMY_LIGHT",
              "next": "N_DUMMY_LIGHT",
              "text": "ask: What happens if it\u2019s light?"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE_DUMMY_BACK",
              "next": "N_REDIRECT_HUB",
              "text": "leave: Back to staging."
            }
          ],
          "id": "N_DUMMY_MENU",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "type": "player_choice"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DUMMY_SEATED",
          "next": "N_DUMMY_SEATED_SUP",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You align the pins and lock the mass in place.\nThe latch resists, then gives\u2014like it\u2019s deciding whether to cooperate.",
          "type": "npc_line"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DUMMY_SEATED_SUP",
          "next": "N_DUMMY_BACK_MENU",
          "speakerId": "BAY_SUPERVISOR",
          "text": "Dummy mass seated. (pause)\nWrite \u201cdummy\u201d on the form. (pause)\nDon\u2019t write \u201ccounterweight for non-local event.\u201d (pause)\nPeople panic. (pause)\nKeep your fingers out of the latch. (pause)\nIt bites.",
          "type": "npc_line"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_OOS_DUMMY",
          "next": "N_DUMMY_BACK_MENU",
          "speakerId": "BAY_SUPERVISOR",
          "text": "No. (pause) AMR first. (pause) Touch the mass. (pause) Before the loop records you. (pause) It reads as untracked adjustment. (pause) Then it\u2019s \u201cinterference\u201d on paper.",
          "type": "npc_line"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DUMMY_ALREADY",
          "next": "N_DUMMY_BACK_MENU",
          "speakerId": "BAY_SUPERVISOR",
          "text": "It\u2019s seated.\nDon\u2019t poke the latch again.",
          "type": "npc_line"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DUMMY_UNITS",
          "next": "N_DUMMY_BACK_MENU",
          "speakerId": "BAY_SUPERVISOR",
          "text": "Who knows. Different hands. Different decades. (pause) Don't chase it. (pause) Make the final number match. (pause) Make it match the last audited number. (pause) If the paperwork doesn't line up, (pause) I'm the one explaining it.",
          "type": "npc_line"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DUMMY_LIGHT",
          "next": "N_DUMMY_BACK_MENU",
          "speakerId": "BAY_SUPERVISOR",
          "text": "If it's light (pause) the system compensates. (pause) The report calls it 'instability'. (pause) That becomes questions. (pause) Then a budget line. (pause) Then visitors. (pause) Seat it to spec. (pause) I don't need visitors.",
          "type": "npc_line"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DUMMY_BACK_MENU",
          "target": "N_DUMMY_MENU",
          "type": "redirect"
        },
        {
          "choices": [
            {
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act2.staging.dummySeated",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": true
                },
                {
                  "key": "act2.staging.testLoadSet",
                  "op": "!=",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "effects": [
                {
